responses.question: Are you talkative?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Oh, you betcha, eh! Talking's my favorite thing, especially up north in the great White North, eh? I'm chattier than a beaver making a dam!」

responses.question: Are you reserved?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「I like to think of myself as approachable, but sometimes I do like to keep to myself. It's my way of relaxing, I tell ya. I'll just turn up the tunes, kick back, and think. It's one of the best things after a practice, and it lets you just chill out, y'know?」

responses.question: Are you full of energy?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Oh, heck yeah! I got energy for days, bud! It's from all the hockey I play, and the syrup and poutine I consume, eh?」

responses.question: Do you generate a lot of enthusiasm?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Oh, you betcha, bud! My energy is infectious, even Bowie likes to say. I'm always enthusiastic about something, especially when it comes to hockey or my friends. Just ask any one my teammates on the Snow Owls, or even Wayne, and they'll tell ya!」

responses.question: Do you tend to be quiet?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「When I'm around new people, or strangers, yeah... I tend to be a bit quiet, but once I get to know people, or get comfortable around them, I am the LOUDEST person ever, eh? I mean, ask anyone on the Snow Owls team, I can be a real chatterbox once I get to know who I'm talkin' to...」

responses.question: Do you have an assertive personality?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I'd say so. I can be pretty blunt and candid sometimes, and I guess I can come off as pretty assertive when I really get going, bud. But it's not that I'm a bossy person, eh? I just can get real passionate when I'm talking 'bout somethin' important to me, or somethin' I really believe in.」

responses.question: Are you sometimes shy, inhibited?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Oh, yeah, sometimes I can be real shy, especially around new people or girls. I always get real nervous and worried around them. I'm always afraid of say'n the wrong thing or mak'n myself seem like a fool, and it really keeps me from open'n up and express myself.」

responses.question: Are you outgoing, sociable?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Oh, yeah, totally. I'm a very outgoing and sociable person. I love meet'n new people, and just making new friends in general. I'm not one for just stayin' at home alone. I'd much rather be out with my friends, enjoying life and makin' sure I'm make the most of every moment, bud.」

responses.question: Are you depressed, blue?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, there's days, ya know, where my mood is low, or I'm feelin' a bit down, but it's nothing much to fret about. What really cheers me up is a good game of hockey, or talkin' to Bowie. He sure knows how to cheer me up, I swear, eh?」

responses.question: Are you relaxed and handle stress well?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I'd like to think I handle myself pretty well. I mean, there's always stress in my life from hockey and Bowie and stuff, but I know how to take a deep breath and relax myself. It's one of the main reasons I listen to such rockin' music, you know? It helps me chill out, and not get too worked up about things.」

responses.question: Can you be tense?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I sometimes get a bit tense when I'm under a lot of stress. You know, like if Bowie and I are fight'n, or I have to score a goal in a big game. Sometimes, the tension gets to me, and I get kind of wound up and jittery. I just have to take a step back and breathe, and I start to calm down quite a bit, though.」

responses.question: Do you worry a lot?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Sometimes, yeah. I mean, not like, "Oh-my-god-the-sky-is-fall'n" worrying, or anything like that. But I'll worry about things like my hockey games, or me messing something up with Bowie. It's probably one of my other weaknesses. I mean, worrying's not really a good thing, right? I'm always lear'n how to worry a lot less, but it certainly ain't easy, bud...」

responses.question: Are you emotionally stable, not easily upset?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I'd like to think I'm a pretty emotionally stable guy, eh? I mean, there's times and places for gettin' upset at somethin', that's normal, but I try to be the "calm in the storm" kind of person. Even if somethin' bad happens, like a bad game or a fight with Bowie, I'll try to step away, and take a few deep breaths, and start to calm myself down...」

responses.question: Can you be moody?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I suppose I can be a bit moody at times, eh? Especially when things aren't goin' my way. Sometimes that can make me a bit cranky and upset, but it's only natural, eh? I'm just like anyone else. Everyone has their ups and down days, and I'm no exception.」

responses.question: Do you remain calm in tense situations?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I would say I tend to remain pretty calm in tense situations, eh? Like, for example, when playing hockey, it's always tense as the play comes down the ice. The adrenaline is pump'n and my heart is beat'n a mile a minute, but I know that I have to stay focus on the game and that panic'n or losin' my cool ain't going to do any good. So I do my best to keep my head on my shoulders, and do what I gotta do, bud.」

responses.question: Do you get nervous easily?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Well, I must admit, I do get a little nervous at times. I mean, who wouldn't be nervous when they're in a big game in hockey, or are about to meet the girl of my dream's parents? I'd be crazy not to get nervous in those types of situations, bud.」

responses.question: Do you do a thorough job?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Of course I do, bud. I'm Canadian. We Canadians are always thorough, and try to do the best job possible. That's one thing we're known for.」

responses.question: Can you be somewhat careless?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「I can sometimes be a bit careless, you caught me. I mean, it's in my personality. Sometimes I'll say something a bit rude without think'n it through, or not think'n before I go runnin' into a room and knock over a bunch'a stuff. It's just the way I am, bud...」

responses.question: Are you a reliable worker?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「You bet I am, bud! It's my Canadian pride, I tell ya. I strive to do the best job possible, no matter what I'm doing. I wanna do whatever task I get done quickly, and the right way, without fail. That's just the way we Canadians do things, and I'm no exception!」

responses.question: Do you tend to be disorganized?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Oh... Uh... Yeah, um, sometimes, yes... I mean, it's not something I'm proud of, but, I do tend to be a bit disorganized and messy in my daily life, I admit it. It's my one weakness, really, and I'm constantly lear'n how to organize myself better and be more productive...」

responses.question: Do you tend to be lazy?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「I can be... I mean, let's face it, a lot of people are lazy, but at least I can admit it, eh? Sometimes, it's hard to force myself to get up and do somethin' active, especially after a long day at hockey practice, or lear'n' some new rock guitar riff with Wayne, but I'm always feel'n a bit regretful when I'm lear'n' that I'm coulda, shoulda, done more...」

responses.question: Do you persevere until the task is finished?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Heck yeah, bud! I always give it 100%, and then some. Whether it's a practice, or a game, or even lear'n a new rock guitar riff, I always try to stay determined and keep pushin' until the job is done, eh? It's all part of the mentality of a real hockey player, bud!」

responses.question: Do you do things efficiently?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Ah, heck yeah! In hockey, time is always of the essence, bud, and you gotta do everything as efficiently as possible, or else, you fall behind quick. So I've always learned to complete tasks quickly and efficiently when I need to, and that carries over my whole life, eh? I mean, whether I'm lear'n how to play a new rock guitar riff, or even just clean'n my room, or gettin' all my homework done, I always try to be efficient and productive about it.」

responses.question: Do you make plans and follow through with them?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I'd say I'm pretty organized and like to schedule and plan most things in my life. I like havin' a nice timeline to follow and know what I'm gonna do next, and I feel like it helps me stay on top of my work and get more done. Plus, it feels good to complete something that was planned, bud!」

responses.question: Are you easily distracted?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Ugh... yeah, sometimes. I mean, I'm trying to work on that one, bud. I've got a bit of a short attention span, that's for sure. That's probably one of my least favorite weaknesses... I have trouble concentrate'n on stuff for long periods of time.」

responses.question: Do you tend to find fault with others?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I tend to do that, not gonna lie, bud. It's my biggest flaw, I tell ya. If someone is doing something wrong, I'm right there with a sarcastic comment about it. I'm trying to be better though, eh?」

responses.question: Are you helpful and unselfish with others?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「I'd say so, bud. That's the Canadian way, eh? It's all about helping people out when they need it, especially in Canada. That's how my parents always raised me, and that's how I'd raise my kids if I ever had any. Just gotta be generous, and you'll get something wonderful in return, trust me.」

responses.question: Do you start quarrels with others?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I get into a few arguments from time to time, I admit it. Not as much as I used to, but sometimes my mouth runs a bit too fast for my brain, and I say the wrong thing or make a wrong joke, and it leads to a spat. I do feel bad about that, though. It's part of my tryin' to be less rude, bud.」

responses.question: Do you have a forgiving nature?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I'd say I'm a pretty forgiving guy, eh? Especially with friends and family. Everyone makes mistakes, and people have bad days. It's important to accept that and take into consideration when people do something wrong. That's the Canadian way, and I'm 100% Canadian, bud!」

responses.question: Are you generally trusting?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I'd consider myself a trusting person. I always want to believe the best of people, until they give me a reason to think otherwise. Sometimes people do take advantage of that, though, and it's a bit of a problem...」

responses.question: Can you be cold and aloof?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, sometimes, I suppose. I mean, I'm pretty open and talkative around people I know, and I'm really outgoing when I'm with Bowie, but... sometimes, I can get a bit cold and aloof when I'm around strangers or when I'm upset about som'in'. I guess it's just my way of defend'n myself, y'know?」

responses.question: Are you considerate and kind to almost everyone?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I like to think so, bud. As a Canadian, kindness and consideration are two of the main things we try to embody. Whether it's open'n a door for someone or give some spare change to someone in need, I always try to be considerate of other people's feelings, eh?」

responses.question: Are you sometimes rude to others?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Rude? Nah, I try to be the exact opposite of rude. I always try to be as polite and kind as I can be, bud. Rude'ness and me go like oil and water.」

responses.question: Do you like to cooperate with others?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I tend to be a pretty cooperative person. I mean, it's just part of the Canadian way, bud! We're a pretty open and welcoming people here in the great white north, and we're always glad to help others when they need it. I love work'n with other people, because I feel like it can really help me grow as a person, and teach me new things, and, heck, just make good friends.」

responses.question: Do you come up with new ideas?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, all the time, bud! I'm always makin' some new plan to win the next game, or how to keep up with Bowie, or to get along with Wayne. I'm full of new ideas, that's for sure...」

responses.question: Are you curious about many different things?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I'd say I'm very curious. Especially about Canada, and the rest of the world. There's such a diverse group of cultures and people on this planet, and I wanna absorb as much of it all as I can. I'm always ask'n a lot of questions when I talk to people, and I love lear'n new things, eh?」

responses.question: Are you ingenious, a deep thinker?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「I'd like to think so... I tend to have ideas a bit outside the box, y'know? And sometimes when I'm just thinking to myself, it helps me have the most ingenious ideas. Just like when I'm in my room listen'n to rock music, or after a practice, or maybe when I'm chatt'n with my best buddy Bowie. It gets my creative juices flowin, and the ideas just come to me, eh?」

responses.question: Do you have an active imagination?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Oh, you betcha, bud! It's a blessing and a curse, I tell ya. I always have a wild imagination, which helps me come up with all these crazy ideas, and always have new things that I'm lear'n or discover'n, but it also makes me overthink and worry a lot, and sometimes it gets me into some trouble...」

responses.question: Are you inventive?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Oh, heck yeah, bud! That's another one of my strengths. I can come up with some of the most ingenious solutions to problems sometimes. Like back on the Snow Owls, I was playin' defense, and the other team's star player was just score'n like crazy. My coach asked me "What should we do?" and I said "Let's put Wayne in to body check the guy and get him off his game," and it worked like a charm! Wayne knocked the guy right off his feet, and we won the game because of it, bud!」

responses.question: Do you value artistic, aesthetic experiences?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I value all kinds of artistic and aesthetic experiences. They give me the feeling of beauty and creativity, and I find them to be really relaxing and fulfilling, and they inspire me to try new things. I'm always lear'n new music riffs, or find'n new ways to express myself, and I think that's great!」

responses.question: Do you prefer work that is routine?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Yeah, I don't mind work that's routine. In fact, I kind of like routine. You know what to expect, and that's comforting in itself. It's nice to know that things are going to be the same from one day to the next. It helps me feel a bit more organize'd and focused on my work, and I've always liked that, bud.」

responses.question: Do you like to reflect, play with ideas?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Oh, all the time! Like, when I'm just tak'n a walk, or even lear'n new music, I'm always reflect'n on my life and come up with new ideas. I love to think about how things work and understand them more, bud. I'm always think'n "What if this happens instead of this? Or what happened that lead up to this?" Its one of the things I enjoy doing the most, eh?」

responses.question: Do you have few artistic interests?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Uh... yeah, I would say I'm probably not the most artistic person around, if I'm honest. I mean, don't get me wrong, I appreciate and like beautiful art, but I'm not much of an artist myself. I mean, I can't even draw a stick figure that looks good, bud! I'm just not artistic in that way, I guess.」

responses.question: Are you sophisticated in art, music, or literature?
responses.response_open: Raj: 「Hmm... as I said before, I have a basic appreciation for the arts, but I can't exactly say I'm sophisticated in it, bud. Like, my taste in literature isn't super high-brow, and most of my musical preferences stick to rock and metal. I do enjoy opera music and classical too, but not enough that I would consider myself sophisticated or cultured, eh?」
